        <p>Our goal for this website is to make the underlying structure of sentences more easily undertstood. When we read sentences we attach meaning to certain words based on arbitrary rules that we've been taught. What we'd like to do is make those rules seem more natural and not as concrete. Language is fluid and often adapting as times change. A great example of this is Olde English. What we see as an antiquated language was once much more commonplace. We'd like to pull the curtain back on the machinery behind English so come along.
