  <div class="container" id="explanation">
    <div class="row row-divided">
      <div class="col">
        <h4>What is a Parse Tree?</h4>
        <p>A <em>parse tree</em> is an ordered, rooted tree representing the structure of a sentence, broken down to parts-of-speech. A tree shows the relationships between words within a sentence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <p>Parts-of-Speech & Shorthand Used:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>NP</b>, a noun phrase</li>
            <li><b>VP</b>, a verb phrase</li>
            <li><b>Det</b>, a determiner</li>
            <li><b>Nom</b>, a nominative</li>
            <li><b>Adv P</b>, an adverb phrase</li>
            <li><b>Adj P</b>, an adjective phrase</li>
            <li><b>N</b>, a noun</li>
            <li><b>V</b>, a verb</li>
            <li><b>Adj</b>, an adjective</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
