      <div class="col">
        <h4>How does this work?</h4>
        <p>As an example, look at the tree to the left. Starting at the bottom, from left to right, you see that “the” and “butterfly” connect to each other as a Noun Phrase (every node between the words and “NP” simply labels their parts of speech). These two words connect as one unit because they are a phrase and, therefore, can be replaced with a single word (the butterfly → it). </p>
        <p>Moving on to the next word, you have “grew” labeled as its own phrase. (You could potentially simplify grew to did and end up with “The butterfly did” or “It did.”) Ultimately these two phrases form a sentence with the NP being the subject and the VP being the predicate. All of these relationships are expressed through this tree.
        </p>
      </div>
